server.js — API routes + multi-household orchestration + import/export; helper domains are split into lib/build-meta.cjs (About/version GitHub Actions metadata), lib/webhook-channels.cjs (Discord/Slack/generic webhook validation + quiet hours + test send), lib/push-subscriptions.cjs (PushSubscription key decode/normalize + caps), lib/reminder-payloads.cjs (Discord/Slack/push overdue + due-today payload builders), lib/store-normalize.cjs (store normalization/defaults), lib/server-dates.cjs (calendar/date helpers + next due), lib/audit-log.cjs (audit row normalization/append), lib/auth-session.cjs (cookie/token + auth middleware builders), lib/csv-export.cjs (CSV export renderer), lib/backup-manager.cjs (scheduled/import backup snapshots + retention), lib/store-access.cjs (registry/sqlite store access, read/write, seed initialization), and lib/reminder-engine.cjs (webhook/push reminder delivery + periodic reminder loop). module.exports includes normalizeStore, buildEntriesCsv for tests; if (require.main === module) wraps listen + Discord reminder interval so npm test does not bind a port or start the timer. Imports buildOpenApiDocument from lib/openapi-spec.cjs; GET /api/openapi.json is public (see requireApiAuth bypass list).

Line references below are approximate; search for symbol names in server.js.

- normalizeEntry(row) — entry shape, choreId, locationIds.
- normalizeChorePreset(row) — validates title/points/color/scoringMode.
- normalizeChorePresets(arr) — array normalization for presets.
- normalizeQuickChoreIds(ids, presets) — validates quick bar ids against presets.
- normalizeStore(raw) — canonicalizes store read from disk (discordWebhook, discordReminderSentAt, pushSubscriptions, auditLog).
- GET /api/audit — recent audit events (auth required); appendAudit on entry/settings/scheduled/import/discord user actions.
- GET /api/entries — list entries + discordWebhook for settings UI.
- Discord / Slack / generic webhooks + Web Push (VAPID): POST /api/discord-webhook/test, POST /api/discord-webhook/remind-now (digest to webhooks and/or push); GET /api/push/vapid-public, GET/POST /api/push/subscriptions, subscribe, unsubscribe, POST /api/push/test; background timer sends overdue reminders per discordReminderSentAt; quiet hours skip both; discordWebhook holds quietHours*, slackWebhookUrl, genericWebhookUrl; store pushSubscriptions (per household, max 24). Env CHORELOG_VAPID_PUBLIC_KEY, CHORELOG_VAPID_PRIVATE_KEY, optional CHORELOG_VAPID_SUBJECT; npm run vapid:keys generates keys; Docker docker/entrypoint.sh + docker/ensure-vapid.sh create data/vapid-keys.env on first run if unset (persisted volume).
- Scheduled chore routes; PUT /api/scheduled-chores/:id supports title/interval/startsOn/reminderEnabled; POST .../complete writes completion entry.
- PUT /api/settings — settings write (people/presets/quick ids/locations/discordWebhook with quiet hours + extra webhook URLs).
- POST /api/import — import handler (replace/merge modes).
- GET /api/export — export.
- POST /api/entries — add entry (supports choreId, locations).
- PUT /api/entries/:id — update entry.

index.html — app shell, dialogs, script bootstrap.

- Settings: Audit log (#auditLogList); Integrations — Discord reminders + quiet hours + Slack/generic URLs (#discordWebhookEnabled, test / post-now) + browser push (#btnPushSubscribe, #btnPushUnsubscribe, #btnPushTest, js/push-notifications.js, sw.js push / notificationclick); nav (#settingsNav, tab panels).
- Analytics filters #analyticsPersonFilter, #analyticsLocationFilter, hint #analyticsFilterHint; then analytics-stats-row / statsGrid, statsGridPoints.
- section-pair: contributions (barsArea, barsAreaPoints) + heatmap taskHeatmap.
- Log form: inChore, #scheduledLogSuggestionsWrap / #scheduledLogSuggestions (due soon / overdue, preset title match), inLocations, quick log.
- log-mom-row: log filter #logSearch, #logList, momGrid, momGridPoints.
- Script: type module src=/js/chore-tracker.js at end of body.

js/chore-tracker.js — thin entrypoint to main.js.

js/main.js — event wiring, auth/bootstrap, mutations, import/export UI flows.

- load() — fetch entries/settings, populate state.
- addEntry() — main add flow; semicolon payload, posts /api/entries.
- fillChoreFromPreset(presetId) — sets #inChore + per-location locations (shared with quick log).
- quickLogChore(presetId) — fillChoreFromPreset then addEntry().
- initScheduledLogSuggestions() — delegated click on #scheduledLogSuggestions → fill + focus chore field.
- saveScheduledStartDate(id, domKey) — updates scheduled chore startsOn from manage-list date input.
- setScheduledReminderEnabled — toggles per-chore reminderEnabled via PUT /api/scheduled-chores/:id.
- Settings shell — initSettingsShell, setSettingsTab, sessionStorage tab key; mobile nav toggle + backdrop for #settingsNav.
- startApp() — init date field, load, pick month, render().
- bootstrap() — session check + app/login visibility.
- #monthSelect → switchMonth (clears log search only).
- #analyticsPersonFilter / #analyticsLocationFilter change → app filters, render().
- #logSearch input → app.logSearchQuery, render().
- export/import handlers (/api/export, /api/import).
- initQuickChores(); initScheduledLogSuggestions(); chore suggest init nearby.

js/presets.js — chore presets + quick log editor + payload resolution.

- syncChoreDatalists() — syncs edit dialog datalist.
- entryChorePoints(e) — points from preset + per_location × locations.
- presetMatchingScheduledTitle(title) — preset match for scheduled log suggestions (exact, then small Levenshtein budget).
- resolveChorePayloadRows(raw) — splits ; and resolves preset ids.
- saveChorePresetsAndQuick() — persists settings to /api/settings.
- preset/quick editors + renderQuickChores.

js/chore-input-suggest.js — custom suggestion list for #inChore.

- initChoreInputSuggest() — keyboard/mouse + segment-aware filtering.

js/render.js — render pipeline for dashboard/log/scheduled views.

- entryMatchesAnalyticsFilters / entriesForAnalyticsMonth — person + location filters for stats/bars/heatmap/MoM (location = entry locationIds includes selected name).
- entryMatchesLogSearch — log-only text filter (whitespace AND tokens).
- countsByPerson / pointsByPerson / taskCountsByDay — use entriesForAnalyticsMonth.
- fullRender() — analytics filters, dual stat grids, bars, heatmap, log list, scheduled log suggestion buttons (scheduledStatus overdue/today/soon + presetMatchingScheduledTitle), dual MoM, scheduled dashboard.
- switchMonth — sets app.currentMonth, clears app.logSearchQuery, render().
- setRenderRenderer(fullRender) registration.

js/state.js — shared mutable app state (app.entries, app.currentMonth, app.logSearchQuery, app.analyticsPersonFilter, app.analyticsLocationFilter, app.readOnly, …).

js/render-registry.js — indirection to avoid import cycles.

js/scheduled-logic.js — scheduledStatus(s) (overdue / today / soon ≤3 days / later); intervalLabel.

js/utils/date.js — date helpers and month keys.

js/api-fetch.js — fetch wrapper with auth redirect behavior.

css/chore-tracker-base.css — reset/theme/shell, top bar, settings dialog (flex scroll, safe-area, dvh), toast.

- :root includes --layout-max-width (820px; widens at 1100px / 1440px).
- .wrap uses var(--layout-max-width).

css/chore-tracker-dashboard.css — .analytics-filters, stats, sections, heatmap, bars, MoM, desktop side-by-side rows.

css/chore-tracker-forms.css — log form, edit dialog, .log-filter-row / .log-search-input, .log-list height (taller at 1100px + log-mom-row).

css/chore-tracker-scheduled.css — scheduled dashboard + dialogs + start-date editor (.scheduled-start-edit) + .scheduled-log-suggestions / .scheduled-suggest-btn.

css/chore-tracker-auth.css — login screen (safe-area, guest card, focus styles, touch targets), Sign in / Create account tabs.

css/chore-tracker-extras.css — chore suggest, preset editors, #inLocations, .log-chore-points.

data/households/registry.db — SQLite household_registry table (per-household scrypt credentials); legacy registry.json is imported once then renamed. data/households/<id>/chores.json (or chores.db when per-household SQLite is enabled) — persisted store (entries, people, …). Legacy root data/chores.json is migrated into households/default/ on first run.


ANALYTICS FILTERS (CLIENT-ONLY)

State: app.analyticsPersonFilter (empty = all), app.analyticsLocationFilter (empty = all). Not cleared on month change.

UI: #analyticsPersonFilter, #analyticsLocationFilter, #analyticsFilterHint above the stat grids.

Scope: task + points stats, contribution bars, daily heatmap, month-over-month (current vs previous month both use the same filters). Does not change the activity log (#logList); use log search there.

Location: an entry matches only if locationIds includes the selected location (entries with no locations excluded when a location is selected).


LOG SEARCH / FILTER (CLIENT-ONLY)

State: app.logSearchQuery (string). Cleared when the month dropdown changes (switchMonth).

UI: #logSearch under “Log for …”; styles in chore-tracker-forms.css.

Matching: entryMatchesLogSearch — whitespace tokens AND; haystack = date, chore, person, locations, points. Only affects #logList.


SCHEDULED LOG SUGGESTIONS (CLIENT-ONLY)

Shown when a scheduled chore is overdue, due today, or due within 3 days (scheduledStatus soon), and its title matches a chore preset (exact case-insensitive, or close fuzzy match via presetMatchingScheduledTitle).

Renders under “Log a chore”, above Quick log. Tap fills #inChore (and per-location selects like quick log); user picks person/date and Add. Does not call scheduled “complete” API — use Scheduled dashboard Mark done to reset the timer.


FEATURE MAP

Auth and server

- Households (multi-tenant): isolated stores under data/households/<id>/; scrypt password hashes per household slug ([a-z0-9][a-z0-9_-]{0,62}) in SQLite data/households/registry.db (Node 22+). Legacy registry.json is imported once then renamed to registry.json.migrated. On first start, legacy data/chores.json is moved to data/households/default/chores.json and the registry seeds household default with password from CHORELOG_PASSWORD (default monkey). POST /api/households (no auth cookie) creates a household when CHORELOG_OPEN_REGISTRATION=1 (body id, password ≥8 chars) or when CHORELOG_MASTER_PASSWORD is set and masterPassword in the body matches; otherwise 403 JSON. 409 if the id already exists.

- Login: POST /api/login with household, username (display name for audit), password; optional guest: true with CHORELOG_GUEST_PASSWORD set on the server issues a read-only session (same person list rules as normal login). Logout: POST /api/logout. Session cookie payload v:2 includes household + user and optional ro (read-only).

- Login members (unauthenticated): POST /api/login/members with household, password — household password or, when guest: true, the guest password (CHORELOG_GUEST_PASSWORD); returns { people: string[] } from the household People list (sorted). Same brute-force throttle as login on failures; used by login UI step 1 → step 2 (pick a person). Does not set a session.

- Registration (unauthenticated): GET /api/register-info — openRegistration, hasMasterPassword, allowCreateHousehold, guestLoginEnabled for the Create account tab and View only (guest) when guest login is enabled. Sign in vs Create account; join = household + password then member dropdown; create = POST /api/households then member dropdown then POST /api/login.

- Account (authenticated): GET /api/account — user, household, sessionExpiresAt, canCreateHouseholds (master password set), openRegistration, readOnly. PUT /api/account/display-name — JSON { user }; re-issues cookie. POST /api/account/password — JSON { currentPassword, newPassword } (≥8); updates this household’s registry password after verifying the current password.

- Brute-force protection: failed sign-ins tracked per client IP (lib/login-throttle.cjs); after CHORELOG_LOGIN_MAX_FAILURES (default 8) failures within CHORELOG_LOGIN_WINDOW_MS (default 15 min), lockout for CHORELOG_LOGIN_LOCKOUT_MS (default 15 min). State in data/login-throttle.json. 429 with Retry-After and JSON { error, retryAfterSeconds } when locked out. CHORELOG_TRUST_PROXY=1 sets Express trust proxy so req.ip reflects X-Forwarded-For behind a reverse proxy.

- Session: signed HMAC cookie chorelog_auth includes user and household and optional ro (read-only / guest); ~30-day expiry; secret from CHORELOG_SECRET (dev default in code). GET /api/auth returns authenticated, user, household, readOnly when valid.

- Read-only enforcement: mutating routes use requireReadWrite after requireApiAuth; if the session has ro, respond 403 JSON { error, code: read_only } (entries, settings, scheduled chores, import, account password/display, push subscribe, Discord test/remind-now, admin VAPID, etc.). Read-only sessions still use GET / export / audit read paths as usual.

- API guard — unauthenticated: GET /api/auth, GET /api/version, GET /api/register-info, GET /api/openapi.json, POST /api/login, POST /api/login/members, POST /api/logout, POST /api/households. Everything else under /api/* requires a valid cookie tied to a known household (requireApiAuth sets req.authPayload, req.householdId).

- OpenAPI (integrators): GET /api/openapi.json returns OpenAPI 3.0.3 JSON; servers[0].url reflects the request host. Source: lib/openapi-spec.cjs (buildOpenApiDocument). Committed snapshot: docs/openapi.json (regenerate with npm run docs:openapi after spec edits). scripts/check-api-routes.cjs ensures every app.(get|post|put|delete)('/api/…') in server.js matches a path+method in the spec (also runs at end of npm test; CI fails on drift).

- When changing HTTP routes: (1) implement in server.js (and requireApiAuth bypass list if public). (2) Update lib/openapi-spec.cjs (paths, components, tags as needed). (3) Run npm run docs:openapi to refresh docs/openapi.json. (4) Run npm test (includes route check). (5) Adjust .rctx Feature map / API guard bullets if behavior or auth changed.

- Persistence (per household): JSON data/households/<id>/chores.json (atomic write). Optional SQLite: if CHORELOG_SQLITE_PATH is set (any non-empty value), each household uses data/households/<id>/chores.db (node:sqlite, WAL); empty DB imports sibling chores.json once. ensureSeed seeds demo data per household when empty.

- Version: GET /api/version — without auth: version, nodeVersion, exportSchemaVersion, multiHousehold, optional gitHubBuild from GITHUB_* or CHORELOG_GITHUB_* env at deploy. With cookie: also household, persistence, databaseRelativePath, optional SQLite engine fields. Footer + Settings About tab.


Data model (store)

- Entries — d, c, p, optional choreId, locationIds, createdAt / updatedAt.
- People & locations — editable lists; at least one each enforced in UI.
- Chore presets — title, points (clamped), hex color, scoringMode flat or per_location.
- Quick bar — up to 24 preset ids validated against presets.
- Scheduled chores — intervalDays, startsOn, lastCompletedAt, reminderEnabled (omit or true = include in overdue webhook reminders), timestamps; next due from last completion or start date.
- discordWebhook — enabled, url (Discord), reminderIntervalMinutes, quietHoursEnabled, quietHoursStart/End (server local HH:MM), slackWebhookUrl (hooks.slack.com), genericWebhookUrl (HTTPS, Discord-shaped JSON); see normalizeDiscordWebhook in server.js.
- Audit log — auditLog[] (id, at, actor, action, target, optional detail); newest first; capped (e.g. 500); one household store = one audit stream.


Chore logging

- Main form — date, person, chore text, multi-select locations (for per_location presets).
- Semicolon bundles — ; separates multiple preset/title segments in one submit; server/client resolve rows (resolveChorePayloadRows).
- Preset resolution — optional choreId + free-text c; points from preset + locations when applicable.
- Quick log — one tap from bar; fillChoreFromPreset sets chore field + locations when none selected for per-location presets.
- Custom suggestions — chore-input-suggest.js: preset picker per segment (query after last ;), keyboard/mouse, color stripe from preset.
- Add toast — success message + Undo (removes last created entries via API).


Activity log (month-scoped)

- List — current month only (from month selector); sorted by date descending.
- Row UI — date, chore text, person chip; preset color left border when choreId set; +N pts and location names when present.
- Edit — dialog with date, chore (datalist), person, locations; PUT /api/entries/:id.
- Delete — confirm dialog; DELETE /api/entries/:id.
- Log search — client-only AND-of-tokens across date/chore/person/locations/points; cleared on month change.


Analytics and dashboard

- Month picker — options from distinct entry months (newest first); drives all dashboard + log views.
- Dual metrics — task counts vs preset points (parallel stat cards, bars, MoM columns).
- Stat cards — totals, most active / top earner, active days, members with activity, balance % (fairness across people), avg points per task (points grid).
- Contribution bars — per-person horizontal bars for tasks and points (separate max scaling).
- Heatmap — tasks per calendar day in selected month; intensity vs busiest day; weekday header; busiest day footer; respects analytics filters.
- Analytics filters — person and location (entry must include location when filtered); apply to stats, bars, heatmap, MoM — not the activity log.
- Month-over-month — previous month vs current for tasks and points; % change with up/down styling; handles no previous month.


Scheduled chores

- Intervals — day, week, 2–3 weeks, ~month, 2–3 months (stored as intervalDays).
- Due logic — overdue / today / soon (≤3 days) / later (scheduled-logic.js); human-readable next due.
- Main dashboard strip — cards with status + Mark done; section hidden when there are no scheduled chores.
- Manage dialog — add (title + interval), list with start date edits, per-chore Remind when overdue (webhooks) checkbox (reminderEnabled), remove; PUT/DELETE routes.
- Mark done flow — dialog picks person; POST .../complete adds log line with scheduled title and resets timer; optional completedDate (calendar day).
- Overdue reminders — optional Discord, Slack (hooks.slack.com), generic HTTPS URLs, and/or Web Push to subscribed PWA devices (VAPID); quiet hours (server local clock, can span midnight); per-chore reminderEnabled; server timer + min interval per chore (discordReminderSentAt); test and post overdue now endpoints.
- Log-form suggestions — buttons for urgent scheduled titles that match a preset (exact/fuzzy); fill chore + locations only; does not complete scheduled item (use Mark done for timer).


Settings and data lifecycle

- Settings layout — tabbed nav (#settingsNav): Interface, Household, Chores, Integrations, Account, Audit, Data, About; About loads GET /api/version (app version, Node, optional GitHub Actions build links when env is set, storage type, data file path, SQLite engine + journal mode when applicable, export schema version); scrollable panel; hamburger + backdrop on small viewports; last tab in sessionStorage (chorelog-settings-tab).

- Account — GET /api/account on open; session summary (household id, display name, expiry, readOnly), edit display name (PUT /api/account/display-name), change household password (POST /api/account/password), optional create household (POST /api/households) when CHORELOG_OPEN_REGISTRATION=1 and/or CHORELOG_MASTER_PASSWORD is set; Log out (POST /api/logout). Read-only / guest: banner + hidden write affordances (js/render.js). js/main.js: loadAccountPanel / loadAccountInfo.

- Integrations — overdue reminders: Discord URL, reminder interval, quiet hours, optional Slack + generic HTTPS URLs; browser push on each device (Settings); Save / Send test / Post overdue now (js/main.js, js/push-notifications.js, server.js, lib/push-send.cjs).

- Appearance — theme system / light / dark (localStorage + inline head script to prevent flash); syncThemeMeta for theme-color (light shell uses cream #f4f3ef for PWA status bar).

- People / locations / presets / quick bar — CRUD in UI; PUT /api/settings batches updates.

- Export — GET /api/export (full JSON backup) and GET /api/export/entries.csv (log rows only, UTF-8 BOM, RFC 4180-style quoting); Settings → Data Export JSON / Export CSV.

- Import — file upload; replace or merge with confirmation; replace triggers a JSON snapshot under households/<id>/backups/ unless CHORELOG_IMPORT_BACKUP=0; imported backup may include auditLog (export v5).

- Audit log UI — Settings → load GET /api/audit on open + Refresh; shows actor (signed-in account) and action summaries.

- PWA — site.webmanifest (standalone); icons: PNG icons/icon-192.png, icons/icon-512.png (install / maskable), SVG icons/app-icon.svg, Apple: icons/apple-touch-icon.png + meta tags; sw.js — installability + Web Push + offline shell: same-origin GET responses cached (/api/* excluded); on network failure, serve cached assets; navigate requests can fall back to cached / or /index.html. Mutations still require network.


Client infrastructure

- api-fetch.js — shared fetch behavior (e.g. auth failures).
- Render registry — breaks import cycles between render and main.
- Responsive shell — --layout-max-width steps at ~820px / 1100px / 1440px; log + MoM side-by-side on wide layouts.
- i18n — localStorage key chorelog-locale (en | de); nested JSON flattened to dotted keys; t(key, vars); initI18n() in chore-tracker.js before main.js; Settings → Language; month names and dates use getLocaleBcp47() (en-US / de-DE).

- Automated tests — npm test runs node --test on test/*.test.cjs, then scripts/check-api-routes.cjs (OpenAPI vs server.js). Tests: normalizeStore (via module.exports from server.js, no listen/timer when required), next due for scheduled chores (lib/scheduled-recurrence.cjs, mirrored in js/utils/date.js), semicolon resolve rules (mirrors resolveChorePayloadRows / matchActivePresetForSegment — exact + Levenshtein when segment length ≥ 4), household registry JSON→SQLite migration (test/households-registry.test.cjs). GitHub Actions: .github/workflows/ci.yml on push/PR to main/master. Further ideas: HTTP import-merge, scheduledStatus labels with i18n stubs.


COMPLETED FUTURE IDEAS

- Brute-force protection — lockout on failed POST /api/login (lib/login-throttle.cjs, data/login-throttle.json). See Auth and server.

- Optional SQLite backend — CHORELOG_SQLITE_PATH, lib/sqlite-store.cjs, migration from JSON. See Auth and server (Persistence).

- CSV / spreadsheet export — GET /api/export/entries.csv, Settings → Data Export CSV.

- Multi-household accounts — isolated stores (data/households/), registry + login household field; POST /api/households with open registration and/or CHORELOG_MASTER_PASSWORD. See Auth and server.

- OpenAPI for integrators — GET /api/openapi.json, lib/openapi-spec.cjs, docs/openapi.json, route drift check. See Auth and server (OpenAPI) and When changing HTTP routes.

- Calendar-native recurrence — scheduled chores support recurrence: interval (rolling intervalDays) or monthlyWeekday with monthOrdinal 1–4 (first–fourth weekday in month) or 5 (last such weekday), weekday 0–6 (Sun–Sat). Shared logic: lib/scheduled-recurrence.cjs / js/scheduled-recurrence.js; UI in scheduled dialog (Repeat + week/day). Server normalizes monthly rows with intervalDays 30 for legacy fields.

- Web Push (PWA) — alternative to Discord for overdue reminders: web-push + VAPID env keys; pushSubscriptions in household store; sw.js shows notifications; Integrations UI enables per device.

- Soft delete — presets and log rows use deletedAt; restore via UI / POST /api/entries/:id/restore; CSV omits removed entries; see js/presets.js, server.js (entry.archive / entry.restore).

- Typo-tolerant semicolon segments — matchActivePresetForSegment in js/presets.js: exact match then Levenshtein (same budget as scheduled suggestions) per segment at submit time.

- Import backups — before replace import: export-shaped JSON snapshot under data/households/<id>/backups/pre-import-replace-<timestamp>.json (skipped if CHORELOG_IMPORT_BACKUP=0). Retention CHORELOG_BACKUP_RETENTION (default 25). Optional interval CHORELOG_SCHEDULED_BACKUP_MS (≥ 60000) backs up all households on a timer.

- Offline shell + guest view — sw.js read-through cache for static assets (see PWA); CHORELOG_GUEST_PASSWORD + sign-in View only (guest) for dashboard/log/stats without writes (requireReadWrite, js/render.js + js/main.js, i18n). See Auth and server and Settings (PWA).


FUTURE IDEAS (IMPLEMENTATION-ORIENTED)

- **Tags or categories** orthogonal to presets (schema + filters + UI).

- **Attachments** — optional image per log entry (object storage, quotas, retention, privacy copy).


